                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-06T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >January 6, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. My telegram number 2, January 6, 11 a.m., Department’s telegram number 1,
                    January 6, noon.<note n="9" xml:id="d420fn9">Not printed.</note> The Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs advises me that conditional upon the call for new elections the
                    Costa Rican Government will extend recognition to the Andrade government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
